specific apps or services.

00:25:55.520 --> 00:26:00.200
So there may be a specific
use case where it's

00:26:00.200 --> 00:26:01.220
useful to do that.

00:26:01.220 --> 00:26:04.450
But for the vast majority of
cases, you should really be

00:26:04.450 --> 00:26:06.660
calling out to the system share
intent-- which, I'll

00:26:06.660 --> 00:26:08.790
show you some examples of
that in just a second--

00:26:08.790 --> 00:26:11.790
rather the hard coding to fire
up a specific app or a

00:26:11.790 --> 00:26:14.640
specific service that
receives sharing.

00:26:14.640 --> 00:26:16.700
I think Android users have just
become really, really

00:26:16.700 --> 00:26:19.350
used to being able to use
whichever application or

00:26:19.350 --> 00:26:20.960
service they want to use.

00:26:20.960 --> 00:26:23.970
And so when they don't
get that, they're

00:26:23.970 --> 00:26:24.685
just going to be unhappy.

00:26:24.685 --> 00:26:27.000
And that's going to be a
frustrating experience.

