00:27:55.110 --> 00:27:58.540
most frequently used application
that you've used

00:27:58.540 --> 00:28:01.360
to share in this particular
application before.

00:28:01.360 --> 00:28:04.810
So tapping on that Share icon
could actually brings down

00:28:04.810 --> 00:28:08.330
this menu, which shows three
additional share options.

00:28:08.330 --> 00:28:11.140
This is ordered by
frequency of use.

00:28:11.140 --> 00:28:15.350
And then if you tap See All,
it'll sort of expand out to

00:28:15.350 --> 00:28:16.990
show you the rest.

00:28:16.990 --> 00:28:18.550
The really nice thing about this
Share Action Provider is,

00:28:18.550 --> 00:28:20.380
it's not going to throw up
this sort big dialogue.

00:28:20.380 --> 00:28:23.550
It feels like you're still
within your application.

00:28:23.550 --> 00:28:27.270
And it's also bubbles up any
of the applications you're

00:28:27.270 --> 00:28:29.330
using the share and orders
by frequency.

00:28:29.330 --> 00:28:33.000
So it does all these things for
you while still letting

00:28:33.000 --> 00:28:34.405
you feel like you're inside
the application.

00:28:39.250 --> 00:28:41.060
And then, down the bottom
here, you'll see for

00:28:41.060 --> 00:28:44.936
developers, to implement this,
a quick tip is to use the

00:28:44.936 --> 00:28:47.330
sharecompat.configure
menu item.

00:28:47.330 --> 00:28:49.020
It does all these things
for you in a

00:28:49.020 --> 00:28:50.270
backward-compatible manner.

00:28:54.420 --> 00:28:56.300
And then the other option is
just to have it as a regular

00:28:56.300 --> 00:28:56.880
share action.

00:28:56.880 --> 00:29:00.810
So rather than an action
provider, it's just a standard

00:29:00.810 --> 00:29:03.380
Action item that goes in
the action bar there.

00:29:03.380 --> 00:29:04.410
So here, you should
just use the

00:29:04.410 --> 00:29:07.680
standard icon like I discussed.

00:29:07.680 --> 00:29:10.890
And then call out to some
standard system share intent,

00:29:10.890 --> 00:29:12.400
which is Action Send.

00:29:12.400 --> 00:29:15.050
And that will fire up this
system dialogue, which goes on

00:29:15.050 --> 00:29:16.750
top of application here.

00:29:16.750 --> 00:29:19.190
And this is what the more recent
version of it looks

00:29:19.190 --> 00:29:21.660
like on, I think,
Jellybean Plus.

00:29:21.660 --> 00:29:24.300
The nice thing about this is
that it's being called by the

00:29:24.300 --> 00:29:26.970
system, so you get this
consistent feel across all

00:29:26.970 --> 00:29:29.740
applications that are creating
